item.description:
This blog introduce how to use ctypes to access C code from Python.
1 C code Here, we use the same C code as my previous blog:
#include &lt;math.h&gt; #include &lt;stdlib.h&gt; #include &lt;stdio.h&gt; #include &lt;string.h&gt; #define PI 3.1415926535 void mycfunc(double *array_d, int *array_i, double d, int i, char *array_c, double *output) { if (strcmp(array_c, &quot;cos&quot;) == 0) { output[0] = cos(array_d[0] + array_i[0] * PI); output[1] = cos(d + i * PI); } elif (strcmp(array_c, &quot;sin&quot;) == 0) { output[0] = sin(array_d[0] + array_i[0] * PI); output[1] = sin(d + i * PI); } } 2 Compile We can use Python to compile the C file into shared library.
